{
    "name": "Woolly Rhinoceros",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> cold plains<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or herd (3\u201312)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The woolly rhinoceros is an herbivore, though unlike its non-woolly cousin it grazes for food rather than browsing on larger plants. The woolly rhino is legendary for its foul temper, and its size and huge horn give it a ferocious bravery. Any threat (real or perceived) to the rhino or its herd is met with loud bellows and the stomping of feet. Often, those who unwittingly anger a woolly rhino have no time to amend the intrusion before the beast attacks."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This large rhinoceros has a shaggy pelt of long, brown fur and a row of immense horns on its snout and brow.</i>",
